				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Piercing, my one procrastination<a name="55430"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 6 04 10:17 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Before Plane of Time, one of the most commonly used weapons by bards just entering the Elemental Planes is the Gold Runed Mithril Knife off Sol Ro, another piercer.  Back in the day, when your guild hit Sleeper's Tomb, odds were the Primal weapon you got as a bard was going to be the spear because only bards and rogues can max piercing all the way to 250 so when the swords and maces dropped, then tended to go to the other melees.  The spears tended to go to bards and rogues.  Bottom line: there have always been good reasons to keep your piercing maxed and honestly, there are not good excuses not to.  Most melee classes have far more than three weapon skills to manage.  Try being a warrior or ranger and maxing 5 plus archery.</span></td>
